# File Handling in Linux

## Definition

File handling refers to creating, viewing, copying, moving, renaming, and deleting files in Linux.

---

## Common Commands

### Create File

```bash
touch file.txt
```

### View File

```bash
cat file.txt
```

### Copy File

```bash
cp file.txt backup.txt
```

### Move/Rename File

```bash
mv file.txt newfile.txt
```

### Delete File

```bash
rm newfile.txt
```

### Display First 5 Lines

```bash
head -5 sample.txt
```

### Display Last 5 Lines

```bash
tail -5 sample.txt
```

---

## Interview Definition

File handling is the process of creating, reading, modifying, copying, moving, and deleting files in Linux.
